# 23 : TESTING — oracle-modes + differential-backends + power-regression
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ THESIS
  testing ≡ multi-oracle against-same-source
  property-based via refinement-generators (§§ 20)
  differential Vulkan↔Level-Zero bit-exact (R18)
  metamorphic algebraic-law-preservation
  power + thermal + frequency regression (R18 sysman)
  hot-reload invariance (§§ 18)
  deterministic replay via {PureDet} + {Reversible} (§§ 04)
  ≡ R18-enabled + R16-anchored

§ ORACLE MODES

  § property-based (QuickCheck lineage)
    @property fn add_commutative(a : i32, b : i32) { a + b == b + a }
    generators derived from refinement-types (§§ 20) :
      usize'idx<N> → bounded-integer-generator
      f32'pos → positive-float-generator
      vec3'unit → random-unit-vector-generator
      Handle<T> from-pool → pool-indexed-generator
    shrinking : auto-derived from refinement-constraints
    seed : deterministic-per-test (replay-safe)
    scale : 1000 cases default, 10k in CI-extended

  § differential (cross-backend)
    given @differential fn target(input) -> Output
    CI runs target on (Vulkan, LevelZero, optionally-D3D12/Metal)
    compares outputs bit-exact for {PureDet}-tagged fns
    tolerance-allowed for non-PureDet (configurable float-ulp tolerance)
    R18 central-test : Vulkan vs L0 on same-SPIR-V
    failure → diagnostic : "backend-X diverges by Δ at input I"

  § metamorphic (algebraic-law)
    for operations with known-algebraic-properties :
      union(a, b) ≡ union(b, a)           // commutativity
      union(a, union(b, c)) ≡ union(union(a, b), c)  // associativity
      @differentiable f : bwd_diff(f + g) == bwd_diff(f) + bwd_diff(g)
      // Leibniz rule : bwd_diff(f * g) == bwd_diff(f)*g + f*bwd_diff(g)
    @metamorphic macro generates equivalence-tests
    stdlib-builtins :
      SDF'L<k> : composition-laws
      Jet<T, N> : Leibniz + Faà-di-Bruno
      FluidGrid : conservation-laws (mass, momentum)

  § power-regression (R18 new)
    baseline stored per-benchmark in .perf-baseline/
    CI runs benchmark with {Telemetry<Power>} enabled
    measure : total-Joules + peak-Watts + avg-Watts
    regression : if > 5% over-baseline → CI-fail
    rolling-median : 3-of-5 runs to reduce variance
    mitigation : sysman reports driver-clocks stable, if-not re-run

  § thermal-stress
    sustained-workload test, duration 5 min
    sample thermal every 100ms via {Telemetry<Thermal>}
    steady-state temp reached < 120s
    max-temp < thermal-limit - 5°C (safety-margin)
    throttling-detected → investigate (not auto-fail unless frequency-drops)

  § frequency-stability
    GPU-clock via zesFrequencyGetState sampled @ 100Hz during benchmark
    stdev / mean < 0.05 (5% stability threshold)
    minimum-freq > 90% of nominal-base-clock
    failure → flags driver-throttle or thermal-issue

  § latency-percentile
    per-dispatch latency measured via {Telemetry<DispatchLatency>}
    histogram : p50, p90, p99, p99.9
    R18 target : p99 < 1µs for L0-immediate-command-lists
    Vulkan p99 typically-higher (5-10µs), still measured + tracked
    regression : any percentile > 10% over-baseline → CI-fail

  § fuzz-with-oracle
    coverage-guided fuzzing (AFL++/libFuzzer style)
    oracle : SMT-derived invariant (§§ 20) — fuzz-input-must-satisfy-refinement
    any input causing panic/UB → stored + minimized + shrunken
    typically : 10 min fuzz-budget per-module in CI-extended

  § replay-tests ({Reversible} + {PureDet})
    record : inputs + initial-state + timing-seed
    replay N-times → assert bit-exact-output-every-run
    cross-machine replay (different CPU-models, same arch) → still bit-exact
    R16 anchor : C99-build replays match CSSLv3-build
    hot-reload-replay : reload-mid-session, then replay, must-match

  § hot-reload-invariance (§§ 18)
    record state S0, perform hot-reload R, record state S1
    assertion : S0 ≡ S1 modulo-schema-migration
    for-all-observable-state preserved
    failure → migration-incorrect or @transient-misapplied

§ TEST-RUNNER
  stage0 : cargo-test for Rust-host + pytest for Python-aux
  stage1+ : CSSLv3-native test-runner `csslc test`
  test-discovery : @test attribute on fns
  parallelism : per-module + per-test configurable
  isolation : per-test fresh-process (for GPU-state cleanliness)
  report : JUnit XML + HTML-dashboard + OTLP-export

§ @test ATTRIBUTES
  @test                 — standard unit-test
  @property             — property-based
  @differential         — runs on multiple backends
  @metamorphic(law)     — algebraic-law-check
  @bench                — performance-benchmark (baseline-tracked)
  @power_bench          — power-regression
  @thermal_stress       — long-duration thermal
  @replay               — deterministic replay N-times
  @hot_reload_test      — hot-reload invariance
  @fuzz(budget_sec=N)   — fuzzing-target
  @golden(path)         — golden-image/output comparison

§ GOLDEN-IMAGE FRAMEWORK
  per-rendering-example : reference-frame in tests/golden/
  CI runs example → compares to golden
  pixel-diff : tolerance configurable (per-percentile)
  SSIM-threshold : > 0.99 structural-similarity
  perceptual-diff : FLIP-metric (NVIDIA) for more-human-aligned
  update : `csslc test --update-golden` after-verified-change

§ CI MATRIX
  platforms :
    linux-x86_64-arc-a770 (primary)
    linux-x86_64-intel-igpu (secondary Intel, cooperative-matrix unavailable)
    windows-x86_64-arc-a770 (primary Win)
    linux-x86_64-nvidia-rtx (Vulkan portability-check)
    linux-x86_64-amd-rdna (Vulkan portability-check)
    mac-arm64-apple-silicon (Metal path)
    browser-chrome-webgpu (WebGPU path)
  backend-variants per-platform :
    linux-arc : Vulkan + L0 (differential primary)
    windows-arc : Vulkan + L0 + optionally D3D12
    mac-apple : Metal
    browser : WebGPU
  schedule :
    per-commit : fast-suite (unit + differential-primary) ≤ 10 min
    per-PR : full-suite (all-oracles) ≤ 45 min
    nightly : extended (fuzz 10min × module + stress 5min × bench)
    release-candidate : full + cross-platform + power-baseline-regen

§ BASELINE MANAGEMENT
  .perf-baseline/ directory per-repo
  per-bench : median of 10 runs on reference-hw
  updated explicitly via `csslc bench --update-baseline` (requires PR-approval)
  stored in git (small-enough — JSON-per-bench)
  drift-detection : weekly-autorun reports trends

§ DETERMINISM ENFORCEMENT
  {PureDet}-tagged fns : bit-exact-required
  violations :
    float-arithmetic order (compile-time-fixed via canonical-IR-order)
    thread-non-determinism (fixed work-schedule required)
    GPU-atomic-order (explicit-sort-before-compare required)
    random-sources ({DetRNG} required, seed-parameterized)
  harness :
    replay N=10 runs, assert all-equal
    cross-backend replay (Vulkan vs L0) when {PureDet}+{Portable}-tagged

§ AUDIT-TESTS (§§ 11 + §§ 22)
  @audit_test : verify {Audit<dom>} events emitted correctly
  check : audit-chain signature-valid
  check : all-declass-events recorded
  check : prime-directive-violations trigger expected-compile-error
  negative-tests : attempt-forbidden-operation, assert-compile-error-with-expected-message

§ EXAMPLES

  // differential + pure-det test
  @differential
  @replay(n = 10)
  fn dispatch_matmul_correctness() / {GPU, PureDet, Telemetry<Counters>} {
    let a = Buffer::<f32>::from_seeded(0x12345, 1024, 1024);
    let b = Buffer::<f32>::from_seeded(0x67890, 1024, 1024);
    let c_vk = matmul_vulkan(&a, &b);
    let c_l0 = matmul_level_zero(&a, &b);
    assert_bit_exact(&c_vk, &c_l0);
  }

  // power regression
  @power_bench
  fn cloud_render_power() / {GPU, Telemetry<Power>} {
    let scene = CloudVolume::load("tests/fixtures/scene_cloud.cssl");
    for _ in 0..1000 { render_clouds(&scene); }
  }
  // baseline stored : avg=187W, peak=215W, joules=31.2

  // metamorphic SDF commutativity
  @metamorphic(law = "union-commutative")
  fn sdf_union_commutes(a : SDF'L<1.0>, b : SDF'L<1.0>, p : vec3) {
    assert_eq!(union(a, b).eval(p), union(b, a).eval(p));
  }

  // hot-reload invariance
  @hot_reload_test
  fn entities_survive_reload() {
    let mut world = World::new();
    let h = world.spawn::<Enemy>(pos = vec3(0, 0, 0));
    hot_reload("tests/fixtures/reload_enemy_v2.cssl");
    assert!(world.exists(h));  // gen-ref + migration preserves
  }

